## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project.

### Implementation Details

**1. Fetched Latest Documentation**
   - Retrieved the official Vercel Web Analytics quickstart guide from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
   - Confirmed this is a Next.js App Router project requiring the `@vercel/analytics/next` import

**2. Package Installation**
   - Installed `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 using pnpm (the project's package manager)
   - Updated dependencies in package.json
   - Generated pnpm-lock.yaml lockfile

**3. Code Integration**
   - Modified: `src/app/layout.tsx`
     - Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
     - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the `</Providers>` closing tag
   - Preserved all existing code structure and functionality
   - Followed Next.js App Router best practices by placing Analytics at the root layout level

**4. Verification & Testing**
   - ✅ Build completed successfully (Next.js 16.2.2 with Turbopack)
   - ✅ TypeScript compilation passed (29.0s)
   - ✅ All 155 tests passed across 9 test files
   - ✅ Static page generation completed (95 pages)
   - ✅ No TypeScript or build errors introduced

### Files Modified

**Created:**
- `pnpm-lock.yaml` - New lockfile with updated dependencies

**Modified:**
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics import and component
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics@^2.0.1 to dependencies

### Next Steps

To enable analytics in production:
1. Deploy this application to Vercel
2. Navigate to your Vercel project dashboard
3. Select "Analytics" from the sidebar
4. Click the "Enable" button

Once enabled and deployed, the Analytics component will automatically track visitor activity. You can verify it's working by checking for Fetch/XHR requests to a unique path containing `/view` in your browser's Network tab when visiting pages.

### Implementation Notes

- The Analytics component is framework-agnostic and works automatically once added
- No additional configuration is required in the code
- Analytics data will only be collected when the feature is enabled in the Vercel dashboard
- The component has minimal performance impact and loads asynchronously
